	<h3>Activation Context (1)</h3>

	A <strong>render request</strong> activates a page. 
	A render request can include parameters, which Tapestry calls the <strong>activation context</strong>.<br/><br/>
	
	To specify an activation context in a PageLink, use the <code>context</code> parameter. 
	Here we have specified <code>context="personId"</code>:
	
  	<div class="eg">
		<t:pagelink page="examples/navigation/ActivationContext2" context="personId">Show Person ${personId}</t:pagelink><br/>
	</div>
	
	The link has a URL similar to this: <code>http://thehost/jumpstart/examples/navigation/activationcontext2/1</code>.<br/> 
	See the activation context appended to the end?<br/><br/>
	
	To pass more in the context, use square brackets and commas. For example <code>t:context="[personId,literal:view]"</code> <br/>
	would render a URL similar to: <code>http://thehost/jumpstart/examples/navigation/activationcontext2/1/view</code>.<br/><br/>
	
	Click the link above to learn more.<br/><br/>
	
